Product-Based Companies
They build and sell their own products (software or hardware) to a broad market.
Revenue Model: Earn money by selling licenses, subscriptions, or packaged solutions.
Requirements come from market research, customer feedback, and internal product teams (R&D teams)

Service-Based Companies
They provide IT services, consulting, or custom software solutions tailored to client needs.
Revenue Model: Earn money through contracts, projects, and billable hours.
Requirements come directly from clients.


